text:
="preserve">Grover Cullen Jennings (April 21, 1939 – June 8, 2020) was an American attorney and Democratic politician. He was born in Sugar Grove, Virginia. From 1982 to 1994, he was a member of the Virginia House of Delegates.
Jennings was killed in a car crash on June 8, 2020 in Johnson City, Tennessee at the age of 81.
